<li id="cite_note-Scientific_Elite:_Nobel_Laureates_in_the_United_States-131"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Scientific_Elite:_Nobel_Laureates_in_the_United_States_131-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Scientific_Elite:_Nobel_Laureates_in_the_United_States_131-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Scientific_Elite:_Nobel_Laureates_in_the_United_States_131-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Scientific_Elite:_Nobel_Laureates_in_the_United_States_131-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Scientific_Elite:_Nobel_Laureates_in_the_United_States_131-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Scientific_Elite:_Nobel_Laureates_in_the_United_States_131-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Scientific_Elite:_Nobel_Laureates_in_the_United_States_131-6"><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Scientific_Elite:_Nobel_Laureates_in_the_United_States_131-7"><sup><i><b>h</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/wiki/Harriet_Zuckerman" title="Harriet Zuckerman">Harriet Zuckerman</a>, <i><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=HAHCzJfmD5IC&amp;q=Scientific+Elite%3A+Nobel+Laureates+in+the+United+States">Scientific Elite: Nobel Laureates in the United States</a></i> New York, The Free Press, 1977 , p.68: Protestants turn up among the American-reared laureates in slightly greater proportion to their numbers in the general population. Thus 72 percent of the seventy-one laureates but about two thirds of the American population were reared in one or another Protestant denomination-)</span>
