<li id="cite_note-188"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-188">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPlavcan2007" class="citation book cs1">Plavcan, J. Michael (2007). "The Invisible Bible: The Logic of Creation Science". In Petto, Andrew J.; Godfrey, Laurie R. (eds.). <i>Scientists Confront Creationism</i>. New York, London: Norton. p.&#160;361. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-393-33073-1" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-393-33073-1"><bdi>978-0-393-33073-1</bdi></a>. <q>Most creationists are simply people who choose to believe that God created the world-either as described in Scripture or through evolution. Creation scientists, by contrast, strive to use legitimate scientific means both to argue against evolutionary <a href="/wiki/Scientific_theory" title="Scientific theory">theory</a> and to prove the creation account as described in Scripture.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=The+Invisible+Bible%3A+The+Logic+of+Creation+Science&amp;rft.btitle=Scientists+Confront+Creationism&amp;rft.place=New+York%2C+London&amp;rft.pages=361&amp;rft.pub=Norton&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-393-33073-1&amp;rft.aulast=Plavcan&amp;rft.aufirst=J.+Michael&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChristianity+and+science" class="Z3988"></span></span>
